    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThere is a lack of API functions related to the window-visible area; such information can only be accessed through `vim.fn`. For example, `vim.fn.line('w0')`, `vim.fn.line('w$')`, and `vim.fn.winsaveview()`.\n\nIn `nvim_set_decoration_provider`, while `toprow` and `botrow` can be obtained via callback functions, they cannot be retrieved directly through the API.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nProvides API functions related to the visible area of a window, such as `nvim_win_get_view()` and `nvim_win_set_view()`, similar to `winsaveview()` and `winrestview()`.",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-17T14:25:24Z",
