        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Another issue with functions like `line('w0') and `vim.fn.saveview` is that they only work on the current buffer and do not allow specifying a window. \n\nTherefore, I believe this is a practical problem rather than merely a matter of standardizing the API. Internally in Neovim, we can use `vim._with{ win = win }` to specify the window, but for external plugins, there doesn't seem to be any guaranteed API available for use.",
            "created_at": "2026-05-07T05:18:34Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39636#issuecomment-4394325221",
