            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> You haven't used `nvim_win_call`?\n\nThere is a pitfall with nvim_win_call: when called in Lua, it only retains a single return value even if the function returns multiple values. Perhaps this is a bug?\n\nEdit: I saw `news-0.10.txt` stated this, not sure why:\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/9174157f7498bb79c51164d94aeaef6ce7508410/runtime/doc/news-0.10.txt#L402-L403",
